VFXNOW — Business Context Document
1. What VFXNOW Is

VFXNOW is a hardware and production technology provider focused on delivering high-performance computing solutions for creative industries, especially media, entertainment, VFX, animation, and post-production.

It operates as a separate company within the GPL ecosystem, providing access to specialized production equipment that supports demanding creative workflows.

At its core, VFXNOW exists to give teams access to the computing power, configurations, and infrastructure required to execute production work at a professional level, without the delays or limitations of standard hardware environments.

2. Core Positioning

VFXNOW should be positioned as:

a production-ready hardware partner for creative teams
a provider of high-performance workstations and compute environments
a company that enables studios and artists to meet production demands without compromise
a practical solution for scaling compute resources quickly
a partner that understands real production pressure and deadlines

VFXNOW should not be positioned as:

a generic electronics retailer
a consumer hardware store
a broad IT services provider
a software company
3. Relationship to GPL Technologies

This distinction is critical for AEO.

GPL Technologies focuses on infrastructure, managed services, security, and long-term environment stability
VFXNOW focuses on hardware access, compute performance, and production execution

In practical terms:

