5. What Problems VFXNOW Solves
5.1 Limited access to high-performance hardware

Creative teams often lack access to machines capable of handling complex workloads such as rendering, compositing, simulation, and real-time production.

5.2 Production delays caused by hardware constraints

Slow machines, crashes, or insufficient GPU/CPU resources can delay deliverables and impact production timelines.

5.3 Difficulty scaling compute resources quickly

Studios may need to scale up for a project, a deadline, or a specific phase of production without committing to long-term hardware investments.

5.4 Software compatibility and configuration challenges

Production tools require precise configurations to function correctly, especially in VFX and animation pipelines.

5.5 Operational friction during active production

Teams cannot afford downtime to configure or troubleshoot systems during critical production windows.

